      <Docs>
        <summary>Checks whether this connection has gone down.</summary>
        <value>To be added.</value>
        <remarks>
          <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">Checks whether this connection has gone down.
 Network connections may get closed during some time of inactivity
 for several reasons. The next time a read is attempted on such a
 connection it will throw an IOException.
 This method tries to alleviate this inconvenience by trying to
 find out if a connection is still usable. Implementations may do
 that by attempting a read with a very small timeout. Thus this
 method may block for a small amount of time before returning a result. 
 It is therefore an <format type="text/html"><i>expensive</i></format> operation.</para>
          <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
            <format type="text/html">
              <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/org/apache/http/HttpConnection.html#isStale()" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
            </format>
          </para>
        </remarks>
        <since version="Added in API level 1" />
      </Docs>
    </Member>
